World Music Day is observed on June 21 every year. It is a day when music lovers and enthusiasts come together to celebrate. The day is known as Fete de la Musique after a music festival that began in France in 1982. The first all-day musical celebration on the day of the solstice was originated by the French Minister of Culture, Jack Lang, and by Maurice Fleuret. Music Day is celebrated in about 120 countries around the world including Nigeria. Below, are quotes from few Nigerian Musicians:       